	   <tr><td>User:</td><td><a href=poster.html?user=122873>Phreda</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td>Title:</td><td id=Guru colspan=1>Guru</td></tr>
	   <tr><td>Journal Rating:</td><td><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 id=headerrow>Bio:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=2>(Disclaimer:  The people, places and events in Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl are as real as they will ever be.  Ficticious names are NOT used to protect the innocent. Some monsters ARE harmed during the production of this journal.)
<P>
Phreda Biggles is proud to be the tank for her family of halfling adventurers.  She'd like to give a shout out to her sisters Phanny and Pheally, and her father Bukko!  Phreda likes to travel, meet people, and slash things into little bits.
<P>
Lemoni Vonhasselhoff used to be a stodgy old fruit, but is getting better now.</td></tr></table></td></tr></table></center>
