	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=10170937836410>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=10170937836410>Aviak huts are for the birds</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=10170937836410#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Mar 25th 5:06 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>__________________________________________________<br><br>Dear Lemoni:<br><br>Potas snuck up to us early today; he gave me a lovely pair of snakeskin gloves and a doll for Rainah.&nbsp;&nbsp;What a swell guy!  So please let Rainah know her dolly is on its way.<br><br>Potas gated away just as someone nearby called out that she wanted to join a group.  We thought that having a third person with us would be a good idea, so we invited her to join us.  Her name sounded familiar.... Then I recalled she befriended you when you trained in Misty Thicket!  I asked her if she remembered you, and she did!  Her name is Ermintrude, remember her?  <br><br>Anyway, we tried to fight the aviaks, but I accidentally irritated an avocet.  He chased us into the Lake Rathetear area.  It was funny - I didn't know my way around South Karana, so Ermintrude was yelling, &quot;go south!&quot;  I fled while fumbling with my compass.  Almost ran into a few trees too.<br><br>Guess who we saw in the entrance to Lake Rathe?  Potas!  That's how he was so speedy in meeting us.  He was horribly outnumbered fighting gnolls, so the three of us helped beat them off of him.  The four of us stayed there for many hours, killing gnoll embalmers, exhumed gnolls and unusually tough skeletons.  They are so disgusting!  Nasty!!  Bleah!  Nevertheless, at least Lake Rathe is active.  There are too many people fighting over too few aviaks in South Karana.<br><br>Anyway, I really liked your friend Ermintrude, and hope to see her again someday.<br><br>Hugs and kisses,<br>Phreda<br><br>P.S. Phanny can resurrect now, hooray!<br>__________________________________________________<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Mar 25 18:57:22 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
