</td></ul></tr></table>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101673488884884>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101673488884884>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101673488884884>Our first taste of South Karana</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101673488884884#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Mar 21st 1:24 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>We had a long day, so I won't write much -- <br><br>Phanny and I took the teleporter back down to Norrath this morning, to land in North Karana.&nbsp;&nbsp;Phanny led me to the gypsy camps so she could bind our souls back on Norrath.  If we had died before she cast the spells, we would have been delivered unto the moon!<br><br>Neither one of us has ever been to South Karana before, and neither one of us thought to find a map first.  We crossed the bridge that separates North from South and surveyed the empty, rolling plain.  Our goal was to find the Aviaks, a race of small birds who were rumored to pack quite a punch.<br><br>&quot;Which way do we go?&quot; Phanny asked.  &quot;Follow me!&quot; I exclaimed, and bounced away. &quot;Do you know where we're going?&quot; Phanny called out.  &quot;Not a clue!&quot;  I giggled, still running.  I was excited to see a new area, and glad we didn't know exactly where the aviaks live.<br><br>We ran up tall hills to get a birds-eye view of the land.  Whenever we saw a large structure, we'd make a beeline for it.  In this manner we discovered a city of Centaurs, a playground populated by putrid undead, and pyramid flanked by wussy skeletons and zombies.  <br><br>The centaurs were entirely new to both of us.  I thought they were only in storybooks!  While they seemed indifferent to our presence on the outskirts of their village, we chose not to risk raising their ire by bothering their people.<br><br>We did, however, knock down two elephants.  One of them nearly crushed Phanny as it sank to its knees in the throes of death.  I took a tooth from one, and Phanny saved a tusk from another.  That tooth is about the size of my fist.<br><br>Phanny was dragging her heels after running ALL DAY.  The sun was setting fast and we hadn't made camp yet.  Luckily, just as the sky was turning purple, we spotted a group of huts with Aviaks.  We hunted a straggler guard before we settled here for the night.<br><br>It's late, we're sure to have a busy day tomorrow!  Yahoo!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Mar 21 13:27:34 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul>
</td></ul></tr></table>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101620200638802>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101620200638802>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101620200638802>/ooc unique experience</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101620200638802#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Mar 15th 9:22 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Derek, (a.k.a. Scrappy, Scrap Dog, TOR!) was practically the first friend we made in Knoxville.&nbsp;&nbsp;We go WAY BACK.<br><br>Anyway, Derek landed a lead role in an indie feature-length film, which had its &quot;world premiere&quot; last night at ValleyFest, our regional annual film festival.  Throwing all hope of a decent night's sleep out the window, we drove to Knox Vegas and met the extended posse at the theater.  Derek was there of course, as were his parents.  <br><br>The movie was ****ing HILARIOUS.  It's a darn good thing it was supposed to be a comedy, because the audience was in stitches.  The last time I heard so many laughs in a theater was for &quot;O Brother Where Art Thou,&quot; a few years ago.  <br><br>The reason I'm bothering telling you this is this:  Derek portrayed a slacker/perpetual college student/video game freak, a true addict.  He couldn't stay away from his computer.  It seduced him with a sexy voice when he was not using it.  &quot;I wish you'd put your hands all over me....  I love how you turn me on....  Let me satisfy you for hours, and hours....&quot; <br><br>His gaming was practically all he talked about with his friends.  He'd excitedly describe in excruciating detail epic conflicts, near deaths; the camera would flashback to Derek and the computer screen.  Meanwhile, his buddies would pretend to stab themselves with their dinner knives.<br><br>And what he was playing? Yep, you guessed it.  I almost squealed when I instantly recognized the first clip, that of an Erudite entering Toxx Forest.  Later there was an extended flashback of a heavy PVP fight.<br><br>It was very amusing for us to sit next to Derek in the theater, watch him on the big screen getting financially cut off from his onscreen parents, and hear his real life parents behind him cheering the onscreen parents.</p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul>
</td></ul></tr></table>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101611893731517>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101611893731517>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101611893731517>Gotta give props</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101611893731517#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Mar 14th 10:17 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>We took a break from fighting the thieves' camp in the Paludal Caverns to sell their former possessions and shop around a bit.&nbsp;&nbsp;Phanny and I wandered into the Bazaar of Shadow Haven.  We were surprised how empty it was!  We never really noticed it before.  Most of the awnings have no merchants under them.  We ran around almost an hour before we found someone to buy from us.<br><br>It gave me an idea though - Phanny and I keep a few of the better pieces of armor when we loot it.  Now that our bank box is almost full, we could borrow one of those awnings in the Bazaar and sell them like merchants do!  Actually, Lemoni might be a better candidate for that.  I'll talk to him about it, and to Phanny too, when she wakes up.<br><br>Oh yeah - we saw the horse stables!  They were beautiful animals.  We even saw a couple of little horses who were the perfect size for us, but they were SO expensive.  We'll probably never have that kind of money.  sigh....<br><br>The next time we entered the Thieves' camp, Foddaman was gone.  That was too bad, it was down to me and Phanny now.  Up ahead an Erudite caster fellow and an Ogre(?) sat quietly on a rock.  Phanny asked them if they were waiting for the thieves to come out, but neither one of them answered her.  We shrugged and walked to the center of the camp.  Big mistake - six or seven thieves surrounded us completely, shouting loudly.  Between the inability to see beyond the circle of thieves around us, and the incredible din they caused, Phanny and I kind of freaked out and ran willy-nilly just to escape!  Unfortunately, Phanny died in the tunnel.  I barely made it back to Shadow Haven with my life.<br><br>We approached the camp a second time with much more caution.  After a few fights, however, the thieves converged upon us like before.  Phanny and I fought like mad, picking off one to find two more replacing it behind us.  Our health drained, the blows we dealt slowed from increasing exhaustion.  <br><br>Then suddenly, some of the thieves started dropping like flies, and a GIGANTIC bear walked up behind Phanny!  I screamed, thinking he was a monster who would swallow her whole.  Phanny gave me a curious look, turned around, and saw the bear.  She screamed too!  We scattered.  <br><br>After screaming and running for a few seconds, we both stopped for breath to discover that the camp was once again quiet. The bear wasn't eating us either.  I sighed hard, then looked over to where we were fighting; the rest of the thieves were dead.  We crept up to the bear and looked up at his steamy snout.  The bear was chuckling at us.<br><br>&quot;Pifpaf's my name,&quot; said the Erudite, &quot;and this is my pal Oddball.&quot;  &quot;Pleased to meet you sirs, you really saved us!&quot; Phanny exclaimed.  I bowed to each of them.  &quot;We'll help you pick off the bandits while we wait for the owlbears.  We need something from them.&quot;  That sounded good to us.<br><br>So for the rest of the day, Phanny and I had two guardian angels.  Pifpaf zotted the thieves so we could save our energy; Oddball the Bear (who was the ogre? from before) healed us during battle.  Phanny meditated sitting UNDER the bear, for better protection.  That looked pretty funny!  He could have squished her flat though, all he needed was to forget she was there and sit on her.<br><br>Oh yeah - one of the Vah Shir thieves had a sweet set of claws.  I pried them from his hands after he fell.  They were of amazing quality.  To my great dismay, they didn't fit!  Argh!  I can't wear them at all.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Mar 14 15:04:00 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
