<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101544996361766>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101544996361766>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101544996361766>I had a nightmare last night.</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101544996361766#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Mar 6th 4:27 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I had the weirdest dream last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;Probably shouldn't have eaten all those meat pies before bedtime.  <br><br>I dreamt I was very tall, much taller than normal.  I felt like me; didn't ever catch my reflection in water though.  (Maybe that's impossible in dreams?)  I could run very fast too, and cast spells.  I couldn't cast on monsters, and actually, I'm not sure what those spells did when I cast them.  It was fun to make all those blue and green lights fly around my body though!<br><br>The landscape was so strange, unlike any place we've ever been.  It was night-time all the time, neither sun nor moon to brighten the pitch black sky.  There were big rocks and little rocks, and plants that looked like skeletons until you walked right up to them.  It felt like a desert, except it was cool instead of hot.<br><br>Phanny wasn't anywhere to be found.  There were little two-legged lizards running around everywhere, and the fattest worms I've ever seen!  They were bigger than snakes.  Little skeletons also wandered around, many of whom carried funny little dolls.  I killed one and put its doll in my satchel to give to Rainah later.  She has wanted a doll for quite some time now.<br><br>Later, I don't know how I got there, but I was someplace where the moon looked so big, it seemed to take up most of the sky!  There weren't many trees around, and they had weird blue leaves.  They dropped fruit which tasted good, but I don't remember their flavor anymore.  <br><br>I walked down a path, trying to find my way home.  Suddenly a skeleton attacked me.  Now, normally, I just swat them away, but he stunned me instantly!  I regained my bearings and fled.  Other skeletons whom I passed started chasing me also.  After a little while, there were at least a half a dozen of them behind me.  I ran and ran and ran, the way you do in nightmares: you feel your legs running, but you don't seem to be able to go very far.  <br><br>I finally woke up with a shudder.  Day was breaking on the Commons. I was glad to see the sun again.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Mar  6 16:28:01 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
