<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101431804236153>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101431804236153>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101431804236153>Crazy kids</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101431804236153#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 21st 2:01 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Guess who I bumped into in the Commons, while slaughtering spiders with an unfair advantage?&nbsp;&nbsp;Rainah!  She looked awful!  She was pale and almost green, and she had bandages all over her legs, arms, and head.  I gave her my sack full of pelts and silks; she was very happy to receive the bounty.  She then asked me where Phanny was.  &quot;She's in Misty Thicket I believe,&quot; I told her.  &quot;Her Barbarian friend needs help surviving the scary goblins!&quot;  Rainah smiled knowingly.  It wasn't too long ago that the goblins in the Thicket posed a danger to her too.<br><br>I asked her why she needed to talk to Phanny, and if I could help with anything.  So Rainah sat down and explained the situation to me.<br><br>Lemoni and Rainah wanted to surprise us with the rest of the weird flesh bits we needed to satisfy Mr. Johannis at the cleric's guild.  They already picked up the zombie sailors' flesh from Wisp Isle, so they ran the very long way from Qeynos, the Karanas, Highpass, Kithicor, and West Commons to Freeport.  My, that was one heck of a trip!  <br><br>On the way, Rainah attracted the attention and ire of a dark elf named Gex(?), who proceeded to zap her to death!  While Lemoni was waiting for Rainah to meet him again, (she had to wait for morning to cross Kithicor,) a strange phenomenon occurred which had everyone shouting and running around in a tizzy!  All of a sudden, hundreds of bixies and willowisps, and some GRIFFONS too, descended upon East Commons and attacked anyone they saw.  Lemoni was unfortunately overcome by no fewer than five willowisps.  He eventually found himself standing next to Rainah at the entrance to Kithicor, both of them mostly naked.<br><br>Anyway, they reached Freeport, and entered the sewers as Phanny and I did earlier.  They had no problem coaxing drowned zombies out of the bottom of the pool (Rainah and Lemoni can both swim a little bit), but after a few fights they were both diseased!  They could not risk another fight while half dead, so they decided to wait for the disease to fade.  <br><br>First, to pass the time, they entertained each other with their illusions.  After that became dull, they decided to practice swimming.  They discovered that if they turned into gnomes, they could swim in shallower water.  After a while they noticed that if they weren't sitting still, the disease would drain their health.  &quot;That's okay,&quot; they told each other, &quot;we always have bandages.&quot;  But then they realized they were OUT of bandages.<br><br>They ran as fast as they could back to Freeport, then split up to ask each merchant for bandages.  The first several had none, and the elves' health dropped to very dangerous levels.  Luckily, Lemoni found a merchant selling bandages in the Arcane Science complex, and bought a sack full of them to split with Rainah.  She sat quietly and waited for him to heal himself and return to her, because she would die if she ran to meet him.  <br><br>They were very lucky they didn't die a slow, painful death!  They were still diseased after their fiasco, and still haven't accomplished their task.  So Rainah decided to fetch Phanny and bring her back to the sewers, to cure disease when the zombies infected them again.<br><br>I wished her luck as she turned herself invisible, and presumably left for Misty Thicket.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Feb 21 14:03:34 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
