<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101308714766712>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101308714766712>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101308714766712>Snuck off and got my butt kicked</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101308714766712#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 7th 9:08 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>As predicted, I couldn't take the peace and quiet and went for a little jaunt!&nbsp;&nbsp;It wasn't until 9:00 p.m. that I left home, a terrible time to run through Kithicor.  So, to pass the time until morning, I ran around Misty Thicket, killing spiders for the silks, wolfs for their pelts, and wasps for their wings.  (I'm helping Blikxen Entopop with his bug collection.)  One halfling offered to sell me spiderling silks for one plat each!  I wasn't THAT desperate, so I turned down his offer.<br><br>Sometime in the early morning, Itaknoir sent me a message telling me he had a present for me!  Woo hoo!  He told me to stick around Misty Thicket, and he would port there soon.  Late afternoon, he arrived and gave me two weapons - a handsome velium two handed sword, and kodiak claws!  The kodiak claws were admittedly a bit less powerful than my current claws, so I tried to give them back.  But he said, &quot;keep them - I sold fifty of them already.&quot;  Well, okay!  <br><br>Then he said, &quot;hold still...&quot;  and started casting a spell.  As the green glow subsided, I felt so different.  I looked down and realized he turned me into a wolf!  THAT WAS SO COOL!  Excited, I ran circles around him, jumping and barking.  So fast, so powerful!  Then I ran back to him and licked his hand, which seemed to be the most sincere thanks a wolf could give.  Halflings heard me shouting with glee and surrounded Itaknoir, all asking to be turned into a wolf too.  He was clearly amused to turn a dozen halflings into wolfs and unleash them into Misty Thicket, so he happily obliged.  <br><br>After saying goodbye and promising to visit him again soon, I ran off toward Kithicor, figuring I still had time to cross it before the undead commenced their nightly rounds.  (To my dismay, I reverted to my normal self by the time I reached Rivervale.)  As I started to run through Kithicor, I realized it WAS awfully dark in there!  It was 8:00 p.m., definitely night time.  I ran as fast as I could to the Commonlands.  Destination:  Nektulos Forest!  I had a score to settle with a certain border guard.<br><br>The border guard wasn't there though!  A gnome in a black robe with a red demon familiar sat where the guard stood before, but he wasn't aggressive at all.  So I decided to find the guard myself.  A path led into the forest, so I followed it in a semi-sneaky fashion.<br><br>After a good long walk I spied two large things.  One was a gigantic tree laying on its side on the ground, apparently chopped down.  The other thing was a stone structure that looked like a tent without the canvas.  And in front of that structure were two guards!  I could tell even from a distance that I would most likely beat them easily.  Then one of them spotted me and started running and yelling.  <br><br>I turned around and let them chase me for a bit. I wanted to get closer to EC before I let him have a taste of hobbit revenge!  Some tall folk passed me and, assuming I was in trouble, starting hitting the guards following me.  Not wanting to lose my prey, I turned around then and started clawing a guard.  The words, &quot;that's all right, I don't need any help,&quot; had not yet escaped my lips when the tall folk ran away!  I was confused by their actions until a third guard ran up and hit me HARD.  Ow!  I glanced down at the pool of blood at my feet and realized I could only survive a few more of his blows.  I limped as fast as I could back to the Commonlands, while all three guards played target practice on me.<br><br>I'm a bit chagrined now, but am determined to see what's in and beyond this forest full of evil, and to see what's under those big guard helmets too!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Feb  7 09:09:13 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
