	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101312244769431>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101312244769431>RE: Snuck off and got my butt kicked</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101312244769431#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 7th 6:56 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85616><span id=Guru>Mistress Lashara</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>183 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Miss Biggles,<br><br>It both dismays and amuses me to learn of your particular interest in our fair city. I thought it fitting to pen this letter in hopes of answering a few of your questions, and perhaps assauge your curiousity without the need for violence.<br><br>Our guards, as you may have already ascertained, and not Drowic themselves. Of course, the only way you might note this is to realize that they are a foot or so taller than Ourselves. Every once and a while, a human from Freeport or Highpass will come to realize the true powers of Hate, and swear his fealty to Innoruuk. These humans flock to Our gates, begging for our enchanters to turn them into Dark Elves, the Perfect Children of Our Great Father.<br><br>Of course, this cannot be accomplished, since humans are not born with the dark blood in their veins and are thus unworthy of Our Form. However merciless you might think We are, the Drow do not openly slay Our brothers in Hate. Rather, we give them a chance to serve us, as pets.<br><br>Outside the dark guilds, in the bowels of Our Great City (which you will never see), is a den of ghouls. These ghouls have taken up residence here as they love to feed on the skeletal pets summoned by Our Heretics. We tolerate their presence as they also keep the place clear of rats. Any human warrior that comes to us is allowed to prove his worth by battling these ghouls. If he survives, he becomes a guard of the forest. If he is found unworthy, he joins the ranks of the many undead to roam the Forest of Eternal Night.<br><br>Humans, as a rule, are inferior to the Drow. They are less intelligent, less agile, less charming and they are generally more crude. Were it not for their brute strength, We would have no use for them at all. But human guards do make lovely pets and if one is slain by a brazen halfing, it is of no great loss to Us. <br><br>In fact, the Drow have pet servants from all the races of Norrath. Do stop by Neriak sometime, and seek me out. I do think you would make a lovely little slave.<br><br>Cordially,<br><br>Mistress Chaesendra D`Morte<br>Ambassador of Neriak<br>Daughter of Innoruuk<br>Childe of Hate<br>Leader of the Order of the Raven</p>&nbsp;<br>Lashara Dyran<br>Keeper of the wolves<br>Ranger of the 54th path<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>"I just find the paths. Knowing -where- they go to isn't in my contract."</td></td></tr>
