<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101294411758758>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101294411758758>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101294411758758>Kids these days....</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101294411758758#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Feb 5th 5:24 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>These last few days have been nice and relaxing, but already I'm eager to set out once again.&nbsp;&nbsp;If Phanny can't come out and play, I might take off without her for a while!<br><br>Not too long ago I saw a young druid in Misty Thicket killing a fire beetle with all the strength he had!  I watched him to make sure he would not be killed, then gave him all the money I had on me (only about 10 silver!).  As I turned to leave, he said &quot;Thank you very much!  Now I can buy a spell!&quot;  <br><br>I stopped dead in my tracks....  He looked pretty unequipped.  But my non-magic-using head forgot that some halflings have to pay for spells on top of everything else.  My heart went out to that little guy!  I ran right back to him and gave him all my food, water, bandages, my fishing pole and all my worms too!  It was all that I had to give him at the moment. He bowed and thanked me again; I practically bounced away.<br><br>That was a while ago, and I still hadn't replaced any of those items.  So yesterday evening, as the sun was setting (always a good time to be outside!) I wandered around town, picking up fishcakes and such to refill my travelling bag.  I wanted to play with my fletching kit too!<br><br>As soon as I wandered into the main square in front of the tavern and bank, I was accosted by no fewer than three halflings, all begging me for things simultaneously!  Two wanted money, and one wanted a weapon.  The fellow who asked for a weapon was already carrying one!  Not only that, but he had some fairly decent looking equipment too.  I couldn't believe his nerve.  I scooted past them all and went into the bank to retrieve my fletching kit.  <br><br>While rooting around in my safe deposit box, a FOURTH halfling tapped my shoulder and quietly asked me for money.  I turned around, ready to start shouting - but stopped because it was a girl.  She said she was a warrior and needed some help.  Well... maybe it wasn't fair of me to help only one, but I felt a kinship with this fellow tank girl.  <br><br>I inspected her to see what she needed, dug around in my bag of looted armor bits, and found a banded mail chestpiece that would fit her.  Sure that she would be pleased with it, I presented it to her.  And do you know what she said?  &quot;Do you have anything for my head?&quot;  She was already wearing something on her head.  It didn't make any sense, and it made me mad.  I replied, &quot;you mean, instead of the banded mail?&quot;  She quickly said, &quot;never mind!&quot; and ran off.<br><br>What is it with kids these days?  Instead of cutting their teeth in Misty Thicket, they bum around Rivervale and bother people.  I never did that, ever.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb  6 07:51:47 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
