	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>/ooc<br><br>After a couple of months of regular updates, Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl is unusually silent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Phreda is taking a temporary rest, while I build Lemoni up to a useful level.  In the meantime, I've posted a few things in Pusbag's journal, which I hope you will enjoy.  My RL sister and I will soon bring our enchanters to 16, at which point we'll go revive the Diminuitive Dynamic Duo.  I can't wait!<br><br>Now that Lemoni has some half decent spells (namely Illusion: Dark Elf, Charm, Choke and Bind Affinity) he isn't as aggravating as before.  A lot of people have said they got tired of their enchanters and deleted them before they even made it to level 12.  Also, after playing him the last week or so, his personality has started to gel.  <br><br>He has four different colors of robes, keeps all of them on hand, and changes them frequently.  He has also developed a fondness for exotic foods, (Arctic Scallops anyone?) and a corresponding disdain for &quot;rations.&quot;  Those aspects, along with his vocabulary, make him seem rather... effete.  But he isn't a stuffy guy.  For instance, the other day, Lemoni was singing &quot;She'll Be Coming 'Round the Mountain&quot; to Rainah as they ran through the Karanas.  I'd make him more of a goofball, but what would people think about a color-changing elf with snooty food and dumb jokes?  Enchanters are hard to solo!<br><br>Some characters are natural extensions of who the player wants to be, or perceives herself to be.  Other characters are opposites of the player's personality, providing a change of pace usually prevented by the restrictions of Real Life.  <br><br>The temptation to single-mindedly powerlevel both characters to obscene heights is strong, but not strong enough to forget that role-playing is part of the fun!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Feb  3 19:58:13 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
