	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>How delightful it feels to take that heavy chainmail off for a while, knock back honey meads at the Fools Gold, and run around the old stomping grounds in my bare feet!&nbsp;&nbsp;I haven't spent so much time at home since I decided to become a warrior.  I'm still working on my fletching.  Mistakes are still pretty common, but I happily lose track of time tying all those little parts together.  And of course, revenge on those annoying bixies is also sweet.  Stupid bixies!<br><br>I finally got to visit with Lemoni.  After dropping off my tradeskill goodies, he went to the orc camps in Misty Thicket to kill time (and orcs) until I arrived.  We spent an afternoon chatting outside, enjoying the lovely weather.  <br><br>I watched him hawk his jewelry; he always kept one eye on the entrance to Misty Thicket while we talked, and gave a shout about his wares when he saw a potential customer wander into town.  On more than one occasion we were surrounded by hobbits a bit younger than me, clamoring for this ring or that bracelet.  He seemed to stand taller when he had customers lined up; he obviously enjoyed getting attention for a job well done.  And his auctioneer's skills have noticeably improved as well.  He has quick and informative answers for any questions about his jewelry, and he usually bowed and thanked each customer heartily.  It made me feel better about where my money was going.  <br><br>Phanny and I have done some serious talking together lately about what we were going to do with ourselves.  Lemoni has already helped us out with his jewelcraft, and his potential is sky-high!  Rainah recently started training to be a tailor. I took my old unused sewing kit out of the bank, and am filling it with silks and pelts to give to her for practice.  <br><br>But other than my fletching, which is really just to kill time while Phanny meditates, Phanny and I aren't doing anything to better ourselves.  Phanny has tentatively decided to try her hand at blacksmithing, and I chose brewing.  If anything we might save a bit of money drinking a river of homebrew instead of the fancy storebought ales and brandies we've grown accustomed to.  I love to drink, but Phanny has raised it to an art form.  She can really pack it away!  And speaking of packing it away, she must carry a whole knapsack of bottles with her. She never seems to run out, and always has some to pass around.  I'd like to eventually surprise her with my own personal brew.  What should I call it.... Phreda's Fine Lager?  yum yum.</p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
