	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101214548730944>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101214548730944>Eagerly anticipated rite of passage</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101214548730944#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jan 27th 11:32 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>We are so happy!&nbsp;&nbsp;For we have finally earned the right to carry our family name into battle and across Norrath.  Bukko would have been proud of us.<br><br>We're STILL in the mines....  We met a friendly, capable group of folks down there, and proceeded to wipe a hundred more goblins off the face of Norrath.  After all this bloodshed, I don't think the Pickclaw goblins could hate us any more than they do now.  (Eh, like I respect their opinion!)<br><br>One of our party members was an Iksar shaman named Comoto.  He was tall, spindly and scaly, and to top it off his hat resembled a cow skull complete with horns.  Phanny took a liking to him almost immediately.  Comoto fell down and played dead whenever we had a few moments to spare, and she thought that was hilarious!  Even after the first dozen times he did it.  It was hard to tell if he was practicing a valuable shaman skill, or enjoying sending my sister into fits of giggles.<br><br>Comoto did assert that playing dead actually saved his life countless times.  At one point, when our numbers were low and the goblins had the advantage, he played dead while the rest of us fled upstairs.  The goblins didn't bother him at all! I wish I could play dead, too.  But when I fall down, I don't usually get back up!<br><br>Grumble grumble - another time, Anulle ran upstairs so the guards could forceably remove a couple of goblins from his back.  I followed him upstairs to help; sometimes the guards don't kill the goblins fast enough and a person can die at the guards' feet.  Unfortunately, I accidentally hit Captain Orben instead of the nearest goblin. Instead of focusing on the goblin, he started hitting me back!  I screamed, &quot;I'm sorry I'm sorry!  I didn't mean to hit--&quot; and died in the hallway.  He should have figured I was aiming for the goblin!<br><br>Phanny now wants to rest in Rivervale for a while.  I'll go back home with her; my new archery equipment will be there any day now, and I'm terribly eager to start playing with it!  I hope to meet Lemoni there this time. I have almost 80 plat to give him from all my efforts in Highpass, so he can work on his jewelcraft some more.  <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Jan 28 12:22:15 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
