	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101196949925464>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101196949925464>Be careful what you wish for....</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101196949925464#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jan 25th 10:39 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>When I got up, Phanny was gone.&nbsp;&nbsp;Figuring she was shopping in the Keep, I fiddled with my bags and baubles.  Then she showed up suddenly and asked me if I was ready to go.  Of course! I exclaimed, and started running to the entrance to Highpass Hold.  Where are you going?  She asked.  We arent going back to the orcs today.  Follow me. <br><br>Instead of going out, we went down  to the mines.  She introduced me to four folk, one of whom was Potas!  We exchanged friendly greetings.  After that, no one in our group saw fit to break the silence except for saying pop when a goblin walked in the door.  I was the tank of course, and the elf in wolf-form also ran up to chew on the goblin.  I dont believe he thought I was doing a very good job.  He was always substantially injured when he meleed, but never stepped back.  And at one point, he cried, dont just stand there, hit him why dont ya?  Im so short, and there were so many people, sometimes its hard to see the monster at hand. I have to make sure Im not trying to hit a party member instead!  That seems like a good reason to hesitate, so my feelings were a little hurt.  I didnt let anyone know that though, I tried as hard as I could to attack as soon as hobbitly possible.<br><br>The goblins were all VERY strong.  If it wasnt for teamwork, someone surely would have died.  But no one even came close to dying.  It was all I could do to maintain the goblins attention!  Id kick, yell, insult and slash them constantly, and the goblins still wanted to attack the casters instead.  I was trying my best.<br><br>After a few hours, Potas and Phanny had to leave.  She suggested I stay with them after she camped; I agreed, and hugged her goodbye between goblins.  The group after Phanny left kept changing. And this was a different kind of group than Id ever encountered before.  I looted a goblin and started divvying up the coins, and one of them said, dont split the money.  I was taken aback.  No splitting?  They agreed to go in alphabetical order to loot the goblins, but only when someone retrieved a brass or ringmail armor piece was it the next persons turn.  I disagreed with that method, but felt there was no room for discussion.  Besides, only a few platinum were at stake, and Ive got enough bandage and ale money in the bank to tide me over for a while.<br><br>And it wasnt long before I realized that I was the least experienced party member by several seasons.  It made me distinctly uncomfortable, as did their lack of conversation.  I didnt even sit with them much; I ran around to find more goblins tucked away in odd corners instead.  Is that how all veterans behave, I wondered?  I stayed as long as I was able, but was very glad to leave.  They werent rude or anything.  I just didnt belong, thats all.  Up at the bank, Maxam tapped my shoulder.  He was awaiting some guild friends to help him retrieve his corpse.  I took off some of my battle gear, sat down with him and had a pleasant chat before I camped for the night.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
