	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Uhhhh, I'm so exhausted.&nbsp;&nbsp;Another day of continuous battle done.  My scarab boots are caked with mud and orc.  I just took them off; I propped my bare feet up on a rock, enjoying the breeze between my toes.  Ahh, comfort.  Get it while you can!  My muscles are better adapted to the claws now, but are still a bit sore.  Not a problem though.<br><br>Phanny is sitting in the corner next to me, (probably upwind, judging by her serene expression) memorizing a new series of spells.  She's been waiting for this moment for a few months now, and is elated now that the moment has arrived.  She bought the spell parchments a while ago and saved them in the bank.  Phanny was right to figure we would be far away from her guild when she became qualified to use the spells!<br><br>Only today did I take my first break from the orc fighting to put my personal bits in order.  I made a trip to the bank accidentally - I wanted to go there eventually, but was actually trying to return to Phanny.  I made a wrong turn at the right time!  What a relief to unload thirty pounds of silver and copper pieces!<br><br>Maxam stopped by late last night and asked me to do him a favor.  Flexing the swell claws he gave me for free, I agreed.  He wanted me to mediate a transaction between him and a monk named Dukle in Rivervale.  Thank goodness only Kithicor Forest separates Rivervale from Highpass Hold, the journey did not take very long.  While I was waiting in Rivervale for Dukle, I stopped at my guild and talked to Marshal Lanena.  She was pleased with my progress and offered to show me how to increase a few skills even more - archery, parry (&quot;what, you mean I can do something besides hit and be hit?&quot;) and the basics of fletching.  Woo hoo!<br><br>I didn't pussy-foot around in Rivervale though, after my training and the favor were finished, I ran right back into the fray.  I hope Phanny will be interested in moving on soon.  I don't like to stay anyplace too long.<br><br>OH!  I forgot!!!  A nasty Shralok orc appeared and immediately attacked us.  Although he was very tough, he could not sustain his life after the six of us surrounded him.  On his body we found a very, very nice bag.  Jeis, a Vah Shir shaman, suggested we roll for it.  I never heard of that before.  It's like gambling, the highest number wins.  And what do you know, I won with a 98!  Beginner's luck I guess.  Even though I horribly coveted the bag, I gave it to Phanny later in private.  She's always being nice to me.<br><br>Orc war.  Orc war... ooh... try saying that five times fast!  heh heh.  I must be tired, I'm not making sense anymore.</p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
