	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Got another letter today!&nbsp;&nbsp;I can't wait for my new things to arrive!  Hurry up Lemoni!<br>_________________________________________<br><br>Phreda,<br><br>As reciprocation of the kindness you have bestowed upon me of late, I travelled the long road to Kelethin in order to acquire the components required to learn the craft of Fletching.  Two knapsacks and a box containing a variety of nocks, shafts, fletches and points are now prepared for delivery to Rivervale.  Through several fletching vendors in Kelethin I was able to glean a rudimentary comprehension of the craft.  It is my hope that this improvised education resulted in sound purchasing decisions.  <br><br>The items yet unobtained are a fletching kit and a bow.  As soon as the fletching kit is purchased, I will forward the entire inventory to you promptly.  You should select your own bow according to your own tastes.  The variety of bows ranges from delicate to brutal.  If you know your preference but cannot locate an adequate instrument in your travels, send me a message and I will procure what you desire. <br><br>My chosen profession is a lonely one.  My skills are not sufficiently advanced as to be coveted by worthy adventurers.  In this nascent period, each land I traverse is either soporifically unchallenging or exceedingly dangerous.  Only because you are a trusted friend could I admit that a willowisp defeated me on the way to Kelethin.  The small, wavering sprite seemed a metaphor for my relative value in this world of giants and gods.  Because of this awareness of my deficiencies, I struggle for achievements alone.  My spirits sag until I recall our friendship.  I thank you, madam.<br><br>Yours faithfully, <br><br>L. Curri<br>_________________________________________________<br><br>Poor kid, he really needs to learn some social skills, and have fun sometimes too!  He's always so serious.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Jan 22 07:52:49 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
