<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101128158923527>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101128158923527>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101128158923527>Warrior training in earnest</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101128158923527#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jan 17th 10:33 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Phanny and I have been fighting in Highpass Hold for more than a week now.&nbsp;&nbsp;Finally we can navigate back and forth to the human town without getting horribly lost!  We even found an inn with some decent food, nestled in the mountains away from the town.  They sell bandages there too, which is good because we've been running through them like crazy! <br><br>The folks we met so far have been very friendly, Maxam being only the first.  We still see him on occasion, though he is now occupied with some goblins in a mine.  The guards and citizens of Highpass even seem to be a little bit friendlier; at least they don't seem outwardly suspicious of us anymore.  They ought to be friendlier by now, for we have killed scores of their enemies, the stinky gnolls!  (The Highpass volunteer force couldn't say the same.  They mostly just stand around and scratch themselves!)<br><br>Sometimes we share gnoll-duty with other visitors in our favorite section of Highpass Hold.  Often the area is empty except for us.  During those times, the gnolls are a little bit more than we can handle, which is just how we like it!  Flame-Paws and Champions arrive to duel us with increasing frequency.  They are challenging foes!  But the more of them, the merrier.  They all wear good armor; their scalps can be turned in to Captain Orben for a few gold too.  Phanny is collecting ex-gnoll ringmail armor pieces for her new friend, a Barbarian shaman.  He is the boy I mentioned earlier.... I tease her about him, but she says he's too tall for her.<br><br>It is during this visit to Highpass Hold that I've finally begun to feel like a real warrior.  The gnolls provide excellent training.  There is little rest between attacks from the beasts, so my skills are in constant exercise.  I am working on the finer points of warrior strategy - how best to taunt the monsters from my sister, how to pull them to our ambush without getting killed.  I'm learning better when to stay and fight to the bitter end, when to run, and how to distract the monsters long enough for Phanny to get out first. I used to be really bad at that, but it's getting better!  <br><br>My training shield is finally resting in the bank.  In its place is Father's club.  The claws are in my other hand, and the club-claw combination looks funny (but not ha-ha funny!).  Maybe it serves as extra distraction to the gnolls!  Anyway, I'm learning how to wield both weapons in battle, and how to strike twice rapidly in succession with the claws.  The training is slow going, but the progress is very rewarding!   In fact, yesterday for the very first time in my life, I dealt a crippling blow to a soothsayer.  Critical hits are fairly common anymore, but I have never crippled anything in one strike!  It was amazing!  <br><br>Being a warrior makes me feel really proud, especially when I'm protecting my sister well.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 24 13:46:58 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
