	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101098041441663>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101098041441663>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101098041441663>Almost flat as a fishcake!</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=122873&mid=101098041441663#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jan 13th 10:53 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>208 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Finally! Phanny's business was concluded. (I suspect it had something to do with a boy, hee hee!)&nbsp;&nbsp;After a bit of hemming and hawing, she admitted that she did not want to go to Wisp Isle and Odus, nor did she want to go to Freeport anytime soon.  I was disappointed until she said she wanted to goof off instead.  Hey, goofing off is good too!<br><br>We eventually decided to return to the gypsy camp in North Karana, and cut our teeth on more of the animal denizens nearby.  Our quarry were mostly scythe and borer beetles, nasty bugs with hard shells and huge pincers.  At one point we were running around the guard tower, and I spied a hill giant in the distance.  Almost simultaneously, someone shouted out a warning about him.   The giant was headed toward the tower! Somewhat alarmed and unsure what to do, I ran into the tower, believing it was a safe place to hide from him.  Phanny chose to hide where she was standing instead.<br><br>I listened to the frightened shouts outside and tried to deduce what was happening.  Then the giant's foot came in through the ceiling and landed mere feet from me! I gasped and leapt away.  The guards were standing at the door of the tower, fighting valiantly against him.  The giant was swinging wildly, and hit me three times before I managed to escape the tower.  Fearing he would follow me to the gypsy camp, I ran straight out into the Karana plains, half blind with terror.  Once I realized he wasn't following me, I veered to the one of the tents and hid inside, gasping for breath.<br><br>Phanny was able to watch most of the carnage from her hiding place.  She told me the giant killed a guard or two before he was vanquished by the survivors.  She gave me the all clear, and I met her at the tower.<br><br>The scythe beetles lost their charm after that, so we decided to leave North Karana.  We wandered over to a bandit camp in the mountains, but quickly determined that they were no match for us!  I did manage to snag a souvenir red sash from one of them before we left.  Phanny wanted to visit the Gorge, but I was tired of the mud men.  Then a candle came on in my head - Highpass!   A challenging territory, one foreign to both of us, and the enchanters guild there exclusively sells a certain spell that Lemoni and Rainah desire.  I owe Rainah a favor anyway, so off we went.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 17 14:39:59 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles, 46 Warrior <br>Inebriator for the Order of the Keg <br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></td></tr>
